⁣
⁣
You can't travel the world and live this lifestyle by playing it safe...⁣
⁣
I took too many risks too many times early on in my life to get to this point.⁣
⁣
I risked precious time with my family by leaving to go to the other side of the country to get an Ivy League education...⁣
⁣
I risked a full ride and a stable career by leaving medical school to start entrepreneurship...⁣
⁣
I risked tried and true 7 figure a year bizs to go build something bigger in the social media world...⁣
⁣
And because of all those risks...I get to live this life today.⁣
⁣
Many of you have the chance to take the same risks and some of you will but some of you won't.⁣
⁣
But make sure as you make your choice...don't worry so much about what could go wrong but instead wonder what it would be like if it all goes exactly how you planned!⁣
⁣
Take more risks. Your future self will thank you one day!

In my mission to keep dropping free game and help people that could really use this info: this week dropped some basics on credit repair. Yes this topic is much more complex; we do 8 figures a year in this space! But let's make sure we educate everyone in these important topics! Info like this can really change someone's life!!

Many people think credit repair is illegal but this is not true. However, there are companies that are doing shady things that you must avoid.

You are allowed by law to validate the accuracy of your credit report and there are actually many protections that make sure there are not inaccurate items on your credit file.

Additionally, if items cannot be proven to be valid then they must consequently be removed from your credit report as well. 

Although you have rights as a consumer...there are companies that operate with shady tactics that could lead you into hot water.

If you are looking to get your credit fixed make sure you work with someone with a proven track record and most importantly ask what their process is.

Make sure they are not filing inaccurate claims on your behalf and filing legal documents or falsifying police reports.

Additionally, any good credit repair company will also have a through terms of service and legal contract. 

There are states that forbid credit repair such as Georgia so make sure the company you work with is in line with any state policies as well. 

For many this may be basic info but let's make sure we spread knowledge to those that need to hear this as well! 

Share this with someone who needs to hear this! And tag them below! 

I don't care what company you use or what you chose to do but I do want to ensure you are always making an educated decision!

It took me a long time to realize this. And for the longest time I thought people who had all these "amazing" things must focus on getting them 24/7 and they must work so hard just to be able to buy them but the truth is it's only the unsuccessful people who fixate on these things and think having them will make them a better person. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sure the cool stuff is cool but really successful people, the people who have all this stuff in immense abundance and can buy it hundreds of times over, could care less about this shit. And once you start realizing this you start realizing that we've been brainwashed to always focus our precious energy on the wrong things and that's what really stops us from getting ahead.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Sure the watches, the cars, the houses are all cool but what really excites someone that's truly successful is mastery, dominating an industry, being renowned in your field, the respect of other subject matter experts, teaching others and uplifting the next generation, being so great at something that you can make money over and over again without having to rely on anyone. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Study the greats and any high performers for that matter and you will quickly realize that they have an immense drive to better themselves and improve their skill sets, their knowledge base, their weaknesses, and everything in between.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So what I'm trying to get at is that if you really want these things you are going to need to put your energy, attention, money, and focus into making yourself the person who deserves all this stuff by focusing on the right things such as knowledge, mentors, courses, coaches, and just being a little bit better each and every day. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And the sooner you realize this the sooner you will actually start achieving the financial results, business results, and life results that you want not to mention all the cool watches and cars you could ever want to buy. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
So as you go on your journey to success and if you find yourself wanting the flashy stuff that's okay. Just make sure you focus on the real things that will get you there and you work on those things every single day. ⁣⁣
⁣

⁣
The fastest way to become a millionaire is to identify the habits that millionaires have have and start adopting them for yourself.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
-Most millionaires became millionaires by having a contrarian mindset. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
By not following the crowd and doing what everyone else is doing. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
And this makes sense because if you believe in efficient markets...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
the idea that as a market or industry becomes saturated and hyper competitive the edge anyone person has disappears...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
this naturally means you must get involved in industries that few people are in and are blue oceans.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
-The second big concept you must focus on is catching trends. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Getting in early on Bitcoin, or e-commerce, or social media could have made you millions even if you weren’t great at it!⁣⁣
⁣⁣
It’s impossible to get into every single trend but like Warren Buffet says you don’t need to hit every single home run you just need to make sure you don’t miss them all. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Start getting educated and aware of what’s happening in the world and start studying what people hate the most. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve found that the things people hate the most end up having the biggest up side when the narrative changes. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Also, start studying what the young generations are thinking and focused on. They drive the trends!!!⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
-Lastly, surround yourself with other millionaires or people who want to become millionaires.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The fastest way to adopt their habits and think like them is to spend time with them. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Make sure you never sleep on investing in events, mentors, and networking. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Aside from eduction...networking will offer you the second biggest ROI in your entrepreneur journey! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Lastly, have patience. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
The fastest way for you may still take 2 years...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve been at this entrepreneur game for so many years now...⁣⁣
⁣⁣
don’t get anxious or quit if it takes longer than you think! Remember what you are working for and never give up on your family or yourself! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Stay positive, keep working, keep learning, and I promise your time will come!

Got to spend a few days in LA handling some biz and also ran up a bunch of money in the financial markets. Life is good when you can live the life you want to live, be around the people you want to be around, and make an impact in the world and have fun while doing it.

I remember riding in Honda civics back in the day and still having the same joy I have for life right now. If you are struggling and you aren't there yet here are my 5 top tips to stay focused and keep working until you get there. 

1. Stay patient. Remember that your goals are big and that's why they may be taking some time. Never get discouraged. Remember everyone started from zero stay focused and never quit and eventually you will get there. 

2. Look for the right people. People are the most important thing and will determine what level of success you have. Even if you have to pay to be around the right people do it! 

3. Always keep learning. One thing I can say is that what I know now is on a entirely different level cognitively then me just a year ago. Always keep learning. The day you stop learning so the day you strip growing. 

4. If you can have fun with what you do then do it. Work is hard. Making money is hard. Success is hard. But if you can get into fields that you enjoy it'll be a lot easier to go the mile and not quit. 

5. You can't catch all investments but you can catch a few. Even Warren Buffet missed Google and Amazon and he's considered the greatest investor of all time. The truth is you only need to catch a few home runs to get rich. There will be many life changing opportunities and you will miss MOST of them. The key is to not miss all of them!

⁣
⁣
You can't travel the world and live this lifestyle by playing it safe...⁣
⁣
I took too many risks too many times early on in my life to get to this point.⁣
⁣
I risked precious time with my family by leaving to go to the other side of the country to get an Ivy League education...⁣
⁣
I risked a full ride and a stable career by leaving medical school to start entrepreneurship...⁣
⁣
I risked tried and true 7 figure a year bizs to go build something bigger in the social media world...⁣
⁣
And because of all those risks...I get to live this life today.⁣
⁣
Many of you have the chance to take the same risks and some of you will but some of you won't.⁣
⁣
But make sure as you make your choice...don't worry so much about what could go wrong but instead wonder what it would be like if it all goes exactly how you planned!⁣
⁣
Take more risks. Your future self will thank you one day!

node.text:
Everyone wants a seat at the table but if you aren't bringing any bread you won't be there for long. 💸

Make sure you become a person of value to others so no matter where the location of the room or table is and no matter who the other people are you will always be able to pull up a chair. 👑

Lead by value and it will always come back to you 100x fold. I've been able to build some of the craziest relationships and network in some of the most elite circles but only because I make sure I give other people much more value than they give me. 💪🏻

That's honestly the blueprint to get into any circle or any network. Give them value first and keep giving them more than you ever take. This creates a positive balance in your relationship bank account so one day when you do need something people always answer YES. ✅

And most importantly, once you get there make sure you put other people onto the game too and try to help them get there as well. There's no point in figuring out the method to the madness and keeping it a secret to yourself. Share the game. You'll be leading with value once again and building your relationship circle even bigger and stronger. 🤝

In my mission to keep dropping free game and help people that could really use this info: this week dropped some basics on credit repair. Yes this topic is much more complex; we do 8 figures a year in this space! But let's make sure we educate everyone in these important topics! Info like this can really change someone's life!!

Many people think credit repair is illegal but this is not true. However, there are companies that are doing shady things that you must avoid.

You are allowed by law to validate the accuracy of your credit report and there are actually many protections that make sure there are not inaccurate items on your credit file.

Additionally, if items cannot be proven to be valid then they must consequently be removed from your credit report as well. 

Although you have rights as a consumer...there are companies that operate with shady tactics that could lead you into hot water.

If you are looking to get your credit fixed make sure you work with someone with a proven track record and most importantly ask what their process is.

Make sure they are not filing inaccurate claims on your behalf and filing legal documents or falsifying police reports.

Additionally, any good credit repair company will also have a through terms of service and legal contract. 

There are states that forbid credit repair such as Georgia so make sure the company you work with is in line with any state policies as well. 

For many this may be basic info but let's make sure we spread knowledge to those that need to hear this as well! 

Share this with someone who needs to hear this! And tag them below! 

I don't care what company you use or what you chose to do but I do want to ensure you are always making an educated decision!

I always knew if I ever made it, I would come back and tell everyone else how they could do it too. 🗣 

Bc when I grew up...there were so many stories of people in the middle of nowhere Alabama with no resources or options but 
somehow made an option of their own... 

There were stories in my city of people who got drafted to the pros... 🏈 

There were stories in my high school of people who went to the ivy leagues... 👩‍🎓 

There were stories of people who started bizs and became millionaires... 💸

But not one of them could be found or reached by any guidance counselor, their old friends, and even sometimes their families. 

Literally 100% of everyone that made it out...disappeared and never was heard from again. 🤯

And the funny thing is after getting many different forms of success myself. From an Ivy League to med school to eventually becoming a multi millionaire 🙏🏻

I realized they prob told people but when no one listened they just QUIT. 

Not on themself but on helping everyone else. 

And the sobering TRUTH is the reason so few go back to uplift the poor is bc we just don't like to listen to anyone. 😤

And if you are someone who has become successful DON'T make the MISTAKE of quitting on everyone else. 

The TRUTH is they probably won't listen to you until you're saying it in front of millions.

But that's Okay. 

The TRUTH is you could even build a billion dollar biz but MOST people would still hate and criticize you.

But that's Okay too. 

Bc out of the millions that you show the way...there will ALWAYS be a few shining stars that actually listen and change their families' lives bc of YOU 🥳

So when you make it...don't be discouraged to share how you did it because of the noise...be encouraged to go back and show people because of the possibilities. 🗣

The TRUTH is everyone reading this will ALL be GONE one day. 🤷🏻‍♂️

And what will be left is HUMANITY. 

So while you're here don't be too focused on yourself to forget to leave an IMPACT on everyone else as a whole! ❤️🙏🏻

May we NEVER forget that FREEDOM isn't FREE and it's a privilege to have the chance to chase our DREAMS in this great country!

My parents came here as immigrants almost 40 years ago...

With the same hope and dreams that so many people come to this country with...

The promise of free speech...🗣

Greater education for their kids...✍🏻

The promise of equal opportunity...⚖️

The ability to do or be anything based on merit...💸

And not be oppressed by anyone but only represented by those that have our best interests at heart. 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

And while many people are upset by what's been happening in this country and they have many reasons to be mad or upset... 😷 

We can't forget that America is still what we make it. It's the greatest country bc people way smarter and forward thinking than any one else decided to make it this way...245 years ago! 

And as we do the most American things we can think of on 4th of July...

Light some fireworks...💥

Grill some grub...🔥🌭

Spend time with loved ones...👨‍👩‍👦‍👦

Pop a few drinks...🍻

Wear some patriotic clothes...🇺🇸🇺🇸

Grab a Cigar or two...

Don't forget that the most American thing we can do is STILL live be the principles our fore fathers set about 245 years ago...

So when the smoke settles and the hangovers are over...and we go back to our day jobs and our daily lives...

Remember that America is only as great as the people in it. So let's do our best to live forth the dream of our fore fathers by being the best American's we can be through our  daily actions we do, the way we treat each other, and how we act as a society. 

So let's be the best versions of ourselves we can be and continue to show the world how great it is to be able to chase our dreams and continue making America the greatest country on this planet. Go be Great! Chase Your Dreams! And pass on the game to the next generation so they can do it too!!
